00:39:34.570 --> 00:39:37.780
working with the Preservation
Research Testing Division

00:39:37.780 --> 00:39:40.580
of the Library of Congress,
and we were trying

00:39:40.580 --> 00:39:43.000
to establish the provenance

00:39:43.000 --> 00:39:45.590
of the printing press itself,
and of the papers used.

00:39:45.590 --> 00:39:48.240
And originally, I was
intrigued by this topic

00:39:48.240 --> 00:39:50.700
because of these Iranian staff
members of the printing press,

00:39:50.700 --> 00:39:53.300
because Iran really learned
the printing press from Russia.

00:39:53.300 --> 00:39:54.780
People were -- had been sent
there to learn the printing press.

00:39:54.780 --> 00:39:56.080
They'd imported the
printing press from Russia,

00:39:56.080 --> 00:39:57.380
and they also would import
materials from Russia.

00:39:57.380 --> 00:39:58.770
So I was curious if -- where
were the materials coming from?

00:39:58.770 --> 00:40:00.070
Were they coming more
from British India?

00:40:00.070 --> 00:40:01.370
Were they coming from Russia?

00:40:01.370 --> 00:40:02.670
Possibly Iran as well, because Iran
started producing its own paper

00:40:02.670 --> 00:40:04.200
in this time period as well.

00:40:04.200 --> 00:40:06.880
What we discovered is that more
or less, the materials did come

00:40:06.880 --> 00:40:10.070
from British India, and we had
a chance to look at a number

00:40:10.070 --> 00:40:14.060
of watermarks that
were in some of these,

00:40:14.060 --> 00:40:17.240
especially "Hijat a Kawia" [assumed
spelling] and "Shamsa Nihar."

00:40:17.240 --> 00:40:18.940
They had wonderful watermarks,

00:40:18.940 --> 00:40:22.320
and all of them came
from mills in London.

00:40:22.320 --> 00:40:24.860
And we believe that this paper
had been sent to British India,

00:40:24.860 --> 00:40:27.700
and then purchased
from British India.

00:40:27.700 --> 00:40:30.630
And this is a good indication

00:40:30.630 --> 00:40:33.270
that the printing press itself
also came from British India.

00:40:33.270 --> 00:40:36.550
It was definitely transported to
Afghanistan through British India,

00:40:36.550 --> 00:40:40.690
and it was prob -- it was likely
created in British India as well.

